AI Invoice Processing Agent (Copilot Studio + Power Platform)
🚀 Overview
This project demonstrates an end‑to‑end AI-powered invoice processing solution built using Microsoft Copilot Studio and Power Platform.
The solution enables users to submit invoices using natural language, automatically validates the input, stores invoice data, and routes high-value invoices through an approval workflow.

🧠 Key Features

🤖 Natural language interaction (Copilot Studio agent)
✅ Automated validation of invoice fields
🧾 Dataverse storage for structured data
🔄 Power Automate workflow orchestration
👨‍💼 Conditional approval process (for high-value invoices)
⚠️ Error handling and user feedback
🔁 End-to-end automation


🏗️ Architecture
User (Chat)
  ↓
Copilot Studio Agent (NL understanding + orchestration)
  ↓
Power Automate Flow (processing logic)
  ↓
Dataverse (data storage)
  ↓
Approval (Outlook / Power Automate)


⚙️ How It Works
1. User Input
User submits invoice via natural language:
Process invoice from Microsoft, invoice INV-400, amount 600, date 2026-06-06


2. Agent Processing
The agent:

extracts required fields:

Vendor Name
Invoice Number
Amount
Invoice Date


asks follow-up questions if needed
asks user for confirmation


3. Validation
Power Automate validates:

missing fields
incorrect values

If invalid → returns error message to agent

4. Data Storage
Valid invoices are stored in Dataverse with fields:

VendorName
InvoiceNumber
Amount
InvoiceDate
Status


5. Approval Logic
If Amount > 5000 → Approval required
Else → Auto-approved


6. Approval Flow
For high-value invoices:

approval request sent via Outlook / Power Automate
flow waits for decision
record updated accordingly


7. Final Response
Agent returns:

success confirmation
approval status if applicable


